text: Neal is an unincorporated community in Pike County, in the U.S. state of Georgia. ==History== Neal was originally named Williamsville; the present name, after landowner H. B. Neal, was adopted when the railroad was extended to the area. A post office called Neal was established in 1886, and remained in operation until 1929. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Pike County, Georgia
title: Neal, Georgia
